message: Welcome, crafter! The key to success is combining extracts. Use the 'vial' on any solid ingredient (magical or mundane) to create a 30-value liquid extract. Avoid using the vial on gas ingredients, it results in negative value. The 'filter' tool can also create 30-value liquids from either magical liquids or magical gases. To achieve maximum scores, combine a MAGICAL liquid extract (e.g., sunstone extract) with a MUNDANE liquid extract (e.g., dandelion extract or frog leg extract) to reach 100 points. Combining two magical extracts typically yields 60 points. Beware of combining more than two items; adding a third often results in negative value. Good luck!

You can achieve 30 points by combining 'filter' with any liquid (mundane or magical) or by combining 'vial' with any solid (mundane or magical). Once you have a 30-value mundane liquid and a 30-value magical liquid, combine them to get 100 points. Avoid using 'vial' on gas items or items that already have a 'botched extraction' feature, as this consistently results in negative values. Also, be wary of combining more than two already processed items, as this can lead to 'overcomplicated' items with negative values.

message: Hey future player! Here are some rules I discovered: 1. Use 'vial' on any solid ingredient (magical or mundane) to consistently get a 30-value liquid extract. 2. Use 'filter' on magical liquid or magical gas ingredients to consistently get a 30-value magical liquid. 3. Combine *two* magical liquid ingredients (e.g., two 30-value filtered/extracted magical liquids) to get a 60-value item. This was my highest consistent score. 4. WARNINGS: Do NOT combine three magical liquids, it resulted in -10. Do NOT combine magical and mundane liquids, it also resulted in -10. Do NOT use 'filter' on solid mundane items (gives -20). Do NOT use 'vial' or 'filter' on already 'botched' items, it worsens their value. Stick to combining two magical liquids from initial magical ingredients for the best results!
